{{etymid|ja|gata-kabuki}}
{{ja-kanjitab|y=k|かた|k1=がた|r=y|alt=型}}

Derived from ''kata'' above.<ref name="NKD1"/> {{rendaku2|sort=かた'|kata|gata}} Found most commonly as a suffixing element in compounds.

The standalone noun sense was originally a shortening of {{m|ja|女形|tr=onnagata|lit=[[woman]] [[form]]}}, a female role played by a male actor in [[kabuki]] [[theater]].  This noun sense is only spelled with the {{m|ja|形}} kanji.

